# PHASE 1 — Runtime Event System

*(Highest leverage system right now)*

Build this before inventory, timers, cinematics, or advanced UI.

## Goal

Allow systems to communicate without directly importing each other.

Right now you probably have:

* router calling renderer
* effects touching state
* runtime orchestrating flow

That’s fine.

But future systems will explode coupling unless you add an event layer now.

---

## Create

```txt id="ys9gg2"
runtime/
  events.js
```

---

## Example API

```js id="0fjs2k"
const listeners = {};

export function on(event, callback) {
  if (!listeners[event]) {
    listeners[event] = [];
  }

  listeners[event].push(callback);
}

export function emit(event, payload = {}) {
  if (!listeners[event]) return;

  for (const callback of listeners[event]) {
    callback(payload);
  }
}
```

---

## Emit Events From:

### router

```js id="jl3f4y"
emit("NODE_CHANGED", {
  from,
  to
});
```

### effects

```js id="qceh4w"
emit("EFFECT_EXECUTED", {
  effect
});
```

### loader

```js id="6j52bh"
emit("HUNT_LOADED", {
  huntId
});
```

### saves

```js id="pt2tvf"
emit("GAME_SAVED");
```

