# One Thing I Would NOT Build Yet

## Full visual editor

Not yet.

You still need:

* stable runtime contracts
* finalized node lifecycle
* mature effect system
* inventory model
* save architecture

Otherwise:
you’ll rebuild the editor repeatedly.

---

# One Thing I WOULD Start Defining Soon

## Canonical Effect Registry

Right now effects are probably open-ended.

That becomes dangerous at scale.

Eventually define:

```txt id="n9k6b7"
effects/
  ADD_ITEM
  REMOVE_ITEM
  SET_FLAG
  PLAY_AUDIO
  START_TIMER
  SHOW_OVERLAY
  GIVE_REWARD
```

This becomes:

* editor-safe
* serializable
* testable
* deterministic

Huge long-term win.

---

# Biggest Strategic Advice

Do not optimize for:

> “How fast can I add features?”

Optimize for:

> “How difficult is it to corrupt the architecture?”

That mindset is why V3 already looks fundamentally healthier than most indie runtime projects.

You are now in the stage where:
small structural decisions matter more than visible features.

That’s the real engine-building phase.
